quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  17,101,"And We indeed gave unto Moses nine clear signs. So ask the Children of Israel. When he came unto them, Pharaoh said, “Truly I think that you, O Moses, are bewitched!”"
  17,102,"He said, “You certainly know that no one has sent these down as clear portents, save the Lord of the heavens and the earth. And truly I think that you, O Pharaoh, are doomed.”"
  17,103,And he desired to incite them from the land; so We drowned him and those with him all together
  17,104,"And We said thereafter unto the Children of Israel, “Dwell in the land. And when the promise of the Hereafter comes to pass, We shall bring you as a mixed assembly.”"
  17,105,"In truth We sent it down, and in truth it descended. And We sent thee not, save as a bearer of glad tidings and as a warner"
  17,106,"and [We sent it down] as a recitation We have divided in parts, that thou mayest recite it unto men in intervals, and We sent it down in successive revelations"
  17,107,"Say, “Believe in it, or believe not.” Surely those who were given knowledge before it, when it is recited unto them, fall down prostrate on their faces"
  17,108,"And they say, “Glory be to our Lord! The Promise of our Lord is indeed fulfilled.”"
  17,109,"And they fall down on their faces, weeping, and it increases them in humility"
  17,110,"Say, “Call upon God, or call upon the Compassionate. Whichever you call upon, to Him belong the Most Beautiful Names. And be not loud in your prayer, nor too quiet therein, but seek a way between.”"
  17,111,"And say, “Praise be to God, who has no child! He has no partner in sovereignty; nor has He any protector out of lowliness.” And proclaim His Greatness"